values: I know I haven't been around in forever, but I had some exciting news I wanted to share. I was just wandering around on kickstarter and saw that there is a project for a fully licensed Stargate Atlantis season 6 in comic book format! I was like holy cow, why have only 25 people donated?? And I realized that maybe the awesome SGA-luvin peeps in fandom didn't even know about it yet. Anyway, if it's something you might be interested in, check out the kickstarter page: https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/882141158/stargate-atlantis-season-six-comic-books Hope all is well with everyone. Miss you guys *hugs*

The pixie and I just finished watching the original Stargate movie and she says it was awesome!  She told me her favorite character is Sha're because she is smart and has a kind heart.

Right now, hubby is showing the pixie "Legend of Mana", and old RPG for the PS2, and she loves it.  She's already proving to be an awesome gamer/scifi nerd just like her parents.  I'm so proud! ;p
Looking forward to a fandom filled new year.  I love you guys!!

Just wondering who's out there lately.  I've been feeling this big whole in my heart and I realized it's this, it's you guys.  This past year, especially the last six months, have been ridiculous.  I'm not going to get into it now; I'll save that for another post, but I miss the closeness and camaraderie I had here.  I want that back, even if I can't seem to find my writing voice at the moment.  *Gathers everyone into a group hug* How the hell is everyone?

Hihi *waves*

I'm kinda sorta around these days.  Things are going well (yay pdoc!) and I'm writing again (SGA even!).  My family is doing well and I'm going to the Supernatural con in Nashville (with specific instructions from my six year old daughter to retrieve Jensen's autograph for her - lol).  What more can a girl ask for? ;)

Hope all is well with you crazy kids!!  I've missing everyone like crazy *group hug*

Things have been pretty stable for me.  I've mostly been watching movies on Netflix.

J is away on a business trip.  The pixie has been making a better effort to listen.

I'm trying to decide what story to work on next.

And that's about it.  Hope all is well with you guys.

Wow, it's been almost three months since I've checked in.  This winter has been pretty rough.  My pdoc ended up taking me off of everything so we could start over.  I was pretty close to ending up in the hospital, but since I was very resistant to the idea, I stuck it out.  I'm back on lithium and sereoquel, plus I'm taking lexapro for the depression, ristaril to sleep, and a prescription B vitamin.  I'm still sleeping a lot the days I'm home alone (I'm only working 2 days a week for the winter), but I'm finally starting to write again.

As a matter of fact, I have almost 12k of McShep ready for beta.  Any takers?  It's the gay resort AU.

How have you guys been?  I hope you all had an awesome holiday season.

xoxo
mckays_girl

We had snow flurries this morning.  It was kinda weird.

In other news, I'm still feeling anxious/restless.  When I'm awake, I don't know what to do with myself most of the time.  I'm still having trouble sleeping, as well.  Next pdoc appointment is tomorrow.  I've been going weekly.  J says he doesn't remember me feeling this bad.  I wish I had happy things to talk about on LJ.  I miss the old days where it was just depression and mania.  At least, I used to sleep when I was depressed and be interested in everything when I was awake and manic.  The lack of interest in most things/ no sleep combo is killing me; sometimes I think literally, but I know that's just the disease talking.  One good thing, since my appetite has been crap, I'm losing weight - about 1-2lbs a week.

I miss writing and I miss being close to you guys.

xoxoxo

Do you ever feel like time is crawling, but it's speedy by at the same time.  I didn't even realize a week had gone by since my last post.

So what's new with me?  We took the pixie pumpkin picking over the weekend and she had a great time (she didn't want to leave).  She's going to be a My Little Pony Pegasus for Halloween.  The costume is adorable.

J and I and still watching Dexter and are partway through season 2.  I wish Netflix had all the seasons set up to watch instantly, but after we finish up season 2 we'll have to start getting the discs in the mail.

Mental health-wise, I'm hanging in there.  I had a bad reaction to the Prozac.  It was causing anxiety and panic attacks so I had to get an emergency pdoc appt on Monday.  I took off from work on Tuesday and Wednesday to let it get out of my system a bit.  I'm still feeling restless, but I think that's mostly boredom.  Also, the ambien didn't help, so now I'm on Restoral (sp?).  It's supposed to be an insomnia drug that helps with anxiety.  I hope it helps because I'm really tired so trying new drugs.  My next appt is Wednesday.

I'm going to try to work of finishing up the edits for the McShep resort au, but I'm not sure how long it will take given the uncertainty of my mental state.  I really wish I was feeling more like I did back in the beginning of joining fandom, but I was stupid manic, so I guess that wasn't good either.  *sigh*

Okay, no more mopey stuff.  Tell me good things that are happening to you people! xoxo

Lots of changes on the med front: switching from Remeron to Prozac, upping the Ritalin and adding Ambien to the mix.  The Abilify is staying the same dosage, but I'll be taking it at night.  Tonight I'll take my first dose of Ambien and hopefully sleep for at least more than two hours at a time.  Pdoc said to take half a dose and if it doesn't work I can up it.  She said I should be feeling better soon.  This morning, I took just the Ritalin, and I notice a difference.  The Abilify makes me tired.

I finished my first round of editing on the McShep resort AU and I'm feeling a little better about it.  I'm about a third of the way of typing up the changes (yes, I edit on a hard copy - for some reason it's easier).  Maybe I'll be able to finish it over the weekend and get it to the beta.

Hubby and I are still enjoying Dexter, even if J is still creeped out - lol.  Is it strange that I don't feel the need to find out if there's a Dexter fandom?  I assume there is, but I'm good just watching.

Pixie is doing well in kindergarten, although she seems bored by the material.  She tries to rush through everything so she can get to the fun stuff.  Sounds familiar. *sigh*  I hope she can learn some patience.  I hope I can figure out how to teach her a skill I struggle with.

Hope all is well with you guys. xoxo

I'm still stuck in this freakin' bout of depression.  I feel so tired all the time, but I am having trouble sleeping through the night.  My psychologist thinks I may not be getting the deep sleep, so my body isn't recharging.  I'm just slugging along right now.  My next pdoc appointment is Monday, where I will beg for something to help me sleep.  I also feel very restless and can't seem to sit still for very long.  I hate feeling like this.  I expend a great deal of energy just going through the motions, just day to day functions, and I'm just so tired.  I constantly have to remind myself that I'll pull up soon and things will get better.

I've been entertaining myself at work with Netflix.  They have a lot of good stuff I can watch instantly.  Today I watched the first episode of Dexter and was creeped out and fascinated.  I can't wait to watch more.

I finished the first draft of the McShep gay resort AU (it's over 11k words), but I'm not sure how I feel about it.  I still have to go through and edit, but I think I might have to wait until I'm feeling better.  We'll see what happens.

I hope everyone is doing well. *hugs*

I didn't even realize it's been three weeks since my last post.  My August "blahs" turned into full blown depression.  I was so busy adjusting to my new schedule, with the pixie starting kindergarten, that I didn't even try to get a sooner appointment with my pdoc.  I finally saw her last Wednesday and she put me on an antidepressant (the name of which escapes me at the moment).  I started taking it Friday night, and I think I am starting to feel a little better.  I hope to be back to "normal" soon.

I've been so bored at work and I can't find the energy to write, or even read much.  Everything feels like so much efforts needs to be put into it.  Luckily, I have netflix, so I've been watching a lot of movies (the watch instantly feature is awesome).  I finally saw Devour, and wasn't really impressed, even if Jensen was good eye candy.  I watched the all three seasons of Avatar: The Last Airbender in order.  It was nice to finally see some of the episodes I missed over the years.  Now I'm watching the last half of SGA season 5.  So far, it's a bit of a disappointment.  I mean, I didn't really have high expectations and I'm disappointed.  Oh well, it helps the time go faster.

My DVR is set to record SPN on Friday night.  I probably won't get to watch it until Sunday, because J and I are usually playing DDO over the weekend (Dungeons and Dragons Online for you non-gamers).  I hope season 5 doesn't suck *crosses fingers*

Well, that what's going on with me.  Hope all is well with you guys.  *hugs*

The end of August was kind of blah for me.  Even though I dropped back down to the previous levels on my meds, I've been bad about taking them consistently.  I haven't been feeling very motivated to do much of anything lately and I feel very stressed about a lot of stuff that I can't control.

The pixie starts kindergarten on Friday and no one has their act together.  I am very nervous about her first day and worry about what will happen.  I know that's a normal feeling, but I am obsessing over it.  I am feeling overwhelmed by simple day-to-day chores and just need a break.  I took Monday off, but ended up doing chores most of the day.

I'm not happy with the story I'm working on; the characterization feels off.  I don't know if I should just take a break and work on sometime else, or just push through.  I kinda wish it was winter and I could hibernate.  I'm sleeping a lot, but I wake up a lot, if that makes sense.

Time to stop rambling. *hugs to everyone*

Oh, and thank you for the b-day wishes and v-gifts.

So, I've given up on the Seroquel, even though my dad thinks I should try 3/4 of a pill.  I've been feeling really tired lately, even without the Seroquel and my therapist reminded me of the side effects of Abilify - tiredness and drowsiness - both of which I've been feeling on the higher dosage.  I've gone back to my previous regiment and feel a little better already.

In other news, I've got 6,000 words of McShep and expect another 5-10k to complete the story.  Also, I have 900+ words of J2 pwp that are in desperate need of a beta.  Any takers?

Hope all is well with everyone. xoxoxo

So, I took 50mg of Seroquel Sunday night and was a zombie when I woke up.  Effects lasted until about 4pm on Monday.  Good news is I slept like the dead.  Hmm, maybe that's why I woke up a zombie.  Last night I cut the pill in half, didn't sleep that well, but woke up alert.  So, somewhere in between 25 and 50mg lies salvation.  Or maybe I just have to get used to the higher dosage.  I see an unproductive weekend in my immediate future.

In other news, I have about 2,400 words written for the SGA gay resort AU and Rodney still hasn't left on vacation.  It's flowing pretty well now that I've gotten down the write first, edit later technique - lol.  I also have another story idea for a sequel to my J2 story.  My muse is is high gear; let's see how long that lasts.

xoxo

The pounds are starting to creep back on, so I really need to get my butt in gear. Here are five things I plan on doing to help myself get back on track.
  1. Stop drinking soda - I shouldn't have started in the first place
  2. Drastically reduce my iced coffee intake (too much sugar!)
  3. Get my ass on the elliptical!
  4. Eat a healthy breakfast every morning
  5. Drink more water
I think, since those changes aren't too drastic, I can stick with them.

I so need a day off just to reset, but I think I'll have to wait a few weeks. *sigh*

I took myself off the Ritalin b/c it was making me high.  I couldn't get any writing done and I was feeling spacy - yay mania.  At today's pdoc appt. I was told it was definitely a good idea to stop the Ritalin for now.  She increased the Abilify and gave me a low dose of Serequel to help me sleep through the night.

The good news is: 1) I am doing well with being aware of my mood shifts and can have the pdoc change up my meds as necessary, 2) once I was off the Ritalin I was able to finish the J2 story.

Maybe now that I know what the problem was, when I go back to working on the SGA gay resort AU, it will come easier.

The pixie starts Kindergarten in t-minus 4 weeks and 2 days.  Where did all the time go?

Hope all is well.   *hugs and kisses for everyone*

Tonight I'm going out on an actual date with my husband - woot!  Cheesecake Factory, some wandering around the mall so I can pic my anniversary present and then the movies (I think we're seeing Inception).  The pixie will be hanging with her aunt and the dogs, so everyone will have a great night.

Today was PT and I got lectured by the therapist, who said I should be using my elliptical and taking better care of myself, so my hips won't hurt as much.  He also said I need better sneakers, with arch support, yadda, yadda, yadda.  Other than the lecture, he was pretty entertaining.  I feel somewhat better after the stretching.  Also, I really miss my trainer at the gym :(

Tomorrow, the accountant needs me to do some data entry, which is awesome because he pays well.  Maybe I'll use that money to go back to the trainer when PT is done.  Sunday, I'm planning on taking J and the pixie to see Despicable Me, which looks hilarious.

I have been distracted from the gay resort AU by J2 porn.  And by distracted I mean I'm writing J2, not reading it (at least, not this very second).  This will be my first SPN RPS.  <lj user="hugglewolf"> is encouraging my decent into Special Hell, as usual.  But really, RPS is probably not as bad as most of my other SPN stuff (*cough*Unicorn!Dean*cough*).  Anyway, it's a quickie and should be done soon.  *\o/*

*hugs to everyone*

Someone is selling a ticket to the Chicago SPN con and I am seriously considering buying it.  I know that if I asked, J would say I should go, but it's so damn expensive.  Plus, there's a good possibility we're taking a cruise in the winter, so I will resist temptation, even if it comes in the form of a photo op with Jared Padalecki *dreamy sigh*  I think I'll put some money away to go to Comic Con next year, because I miss seeing everyone =D

I think I'm ready for a new tattoo, though.  I mean, I know exactly what I want; it's pictured in great detail in my brain.  I just have to find the right artist to capture that image and ink it on my lower back.
OMG, if you haven't read every second tuesday, go and do it now. It's J2 with office worker!Jensen and masseuse!Jared and is ridiculously hot and funny and why are you still here? - go read!!

1. Today is my 10 year wedding anniversary!
  2. Friday, I'm going out to celebrate with J!
  3. The sun is shining and the weather is mild.
  4. The surprise party for J's 36th b-day was very successful. A good time was had by all.
  5. I'm going to have lunch with my other half in a few minutes. =D
  6. We might be getting a dog. Does anyone know anything about psychiatric service dogs?
  7. Disney cruises are way more affordable than I thought; so that might be our winter vacation.
  8. Got a notice from FedEx that my pool is waiting for me on the back step. Soon I'll be swimming with the pixie!
  9. I'll be starting physical therapy for my hips on Friday. I should only need a few weeks, and then I'll be able to work on my own.
  10. I'm feeling really good right now. It may be the caffeine from my Cherry Pepsi, or it may just be me. ;p

1. I have the best family in the whole world!
  2. My 10 year anniversary is Tuesday =D
  3. I have three people looking over my Sam/Dean genderswap story right now.
  4. There will be McShep in the future! I have actually begun writing the gay resort AU!!
  5. I am loving all the free v-gifts LJ is allowing the paid members. They're way cute!
  6. Going to finally get an eye exam today (and probably new glasses), so I can see better.
  7. Orthopedist appointment is at 2:30pm today.
  8. I had creme brulee flavored creamer in my coffee this morning.
  9. It's warm and sunny!
  10. I had 8 hours of sleep.

Wow, it's been almost 2 weeks since I last updated. Where did the time go? Well, some of it was spent in Florida on a family vacation, which was pretty awesome. My in-laws mostly behaved and the pixie had a super fab time. We took her to Disney World one day and Universal Studio's Islands of Adventure another day. The rest of the time was spent swimming and BBQing and chillaxing with family. For those who have never been there, Universal's IoA has a Dr. Seuss section and a comic book section (among the other cool areas). How awesome is it that the pixie was pointing and yelling, "Look mom, it's Wolverine and look, it's Spiderman"? I let her choose two souvenirs and she picked a plush Cat in the Hat and a plush Superhero Squad Hulk. Plus, J let her pick out her very first comic book. She got one based on The Superhero Squad Show. I love that she's really interested in a lot of the same stuff we are =D The only bad part about the vacation was that because of all the walking, my whole body is out of whack. I was born with dislocated hips and the left ball and socket are malformed. I have minor pain from time to time, and lots of walking usually has me sore for days. Now, the left side keeps locking up and I get shocks of intense pain. I went and got a massage last week and I have an appointment with an orthopedist on Wednesday, so I know I'll get everything taken care of soon. Now my in-laws are talking about a cruise. I get to pick it based on what we can afford, which is nice. I'm gonna have to do a lot of research and budgeting to find the perfect family friendly cruise, but I'm sure I can find something everyone will enjoy. Also, I just want to say that the Abilify/Ritalin combo is really working for me. Hopefully, I won't have to change anything come the winter. And speaking of winter, I already know that I'll be working part time again, so I think I'll do better with a few months to prepare, instead of getting it sprung on me at the company xmas party like last year. Last night I finished writing and editing the Sam/Dean genderswap story. It's just over 25,000 words and I am totally, ridiculously in love with what I accomplished. I sent it off to for beta, and would really love to find an extra person to look it over because it's so long. Any volunteers? *bats eyelashes* That's what I've been up to. Right now the sky is darkening and a storm is rolling in. I hope there's thunder and lightning =D I'm waiting for UPS to show up with a package (yay new cross-cut shredder - yes I'm a dork) and then I'm pretty much done with work for the day and will have to amuse myself with youtube and J2 bigbang. Yes, life is good ;p I'm tying to decide if I should start another story, or wait until the new one is posted. What say you guys? xoxox

I had a very pleasant weekend with hubby and the pixie.  Friday I surprised them both: pixie got to hang with her aunt and a gang of dogs, and I took J to see Airbender.  The movie was a disappointment (we're big fans of the series) but the company was great.  Saturday we lounged around until 5pm and went to see UFC at a friend's house.  Sunday we took the pixie to the mall so she could spend her birthday money on a pillow pet and then she treated us to ice cream with her Friendlys gift card.  Monday it was too hot to move - we even popped the circuit breakers b/c all the ACs were on.

Today the pixie started summer camp and she was nervous at first, but I think she's be fine.  Thursday we're leaving for FL and we're all so excited about this vacation.  She'll finally get to meet her cousins - my bro-in-law & family got shipped off to Hawaii a few weeks before she was born (he's in the navy).  Now that they're on the mainland it's time for a family get together.

I'm just shy of 20,000 words and there's finally some sexing in my story - yay!  Actually, I'm in the middle of the sex scene and Dean is a little miffed that I stopped to do other things.  I still have another 2 sections left on my outline that have to be written, so I'm anticipating another 5-10,000 words.  <lj user="hugglewolf"> was awesome enough to take a peak around the 15k mark and is itching for more (which makes me deliriously happy).  Anyone want to join her for beta duties?

Hope my American compatriots had a great July 4th and that all is well with everyone.
xoxo
McKay

Pixie party was a success.  Now if I can only build an addition onto the house to make room for all her stuff.

Started taking the Abilify and I haven't noticed a difference yet.  Maybe the dose is too low.  Pdoc said I can double it if I don't have a problem with side effects.  So far, so good on that end.

My sister is going to watch the pixie tonight so J can come with me to therapy.  I want to work on our communication skills, among other things, because I'm tired of things feeling off.

I've crossed the 15,000 word mark on my latest Sam/Dean story.  I think I'm about half way done.  Not sure when it'll be completed, but I was wondering who would be up for helping with beta duties (the more the merrier).  It's NC-17 with some girl!Sam/Dean.

*hugs*

Well, it's already Wednesday; the week is flying by.

Tonight the pixie has her pre-school graduation.  I finally figured out how to work the new video camera (which is ridiculously easy to operate once you actually take it out of the box).  I'm supposed to pick her up early at 4pm and be back by 6:30 for the ceremony.  While we're waiting, we're going to head to Red Lobster for dinner so she can fill her tummy with popcorn shrimp.

Her birthday party is this Saturday and I am so glad we are not having it at my house with 25 kids showing up.  The pixie is super excited that her home friends and school friends will get to hang out.

We have a family vacation planned for July 8th - heading to Florida to see the in-laws.  It's going to be pretty entertaining, since J's brother will also be bringing his family.  J's mom is insisting that we all stay at the house.  There are two guest bedrooms and the kids will sleep in the living room.  Oh, did I mention that my bro and sis-in-law have 4 kids of their own?  Three girls -5, 7 & 12, plus a 16 year old boy.  I don't think there will be much sleeping with all the giggling that I predict we'll be hearing.  I feel sorry for my poor nephew, but it'll still be pretty hilarious.  We're planning on taking the kids to Disney and Universal, and maybe chilling out at the beach (or chillaxing as the pixie says).  As long as my mother-in-law keeps her comments about my weight to herself, all will be well.

On the writing front things have been awesome.  Last week, I think I wrote about 3,000 words and might already be past that this week.  It may be to the lack of lithium, or maybe the phase of the moon, who knows.  I'm just happy to be making progress.  I filled my prescription for Abilify, but haven't started it yet.  I want to wait for a day I have nothing planned, in case there are weird side-effects.  So, Sunday I'll give it a try.

Other than that, things have been quiet.  No one has injured themselves, the pixie's behavior has been improving, and I'm feeling pretty in control of everything.  In a few weeks, our schedule will be less hectic and I'll be able to enjoy a stress-free summer. =D

The muse feels that it is perfectly acceptable to get distracted by shiny SPN big bang fic instead of typing up what I wrote today (and possibly writing more).  It was 35,000 words of J2 porn, people, how could I resist?  Also, is it possible to have a crush on Jared's hands, like totally separate from my crush on Jared?  Just saying ;p

Also, also, I forgot to mention that there are freakin' adorable lemurs on my profile page and they amuse me greatly.  Many thanks to <lj user="ariadne83">, <lj user="girly_curl_3"> and <lj user="adafrog">!!

Now off to bed with happy thoughts.  Sweet dreams, my darlings *mwah*

I popped a Ritalin around lunch time and my muse is very happy with this.  Almost seven pages later (hand written - am I the only one who still does that?), and I feel pretty damn accomplished.  I just hope the Abilify doesn't mess with the muse's new-found mojo.  Only problem is that my hands are having trouble keeping up with my brain when I type, and I type at a pretty decent speed, so I have to make a lot of corrections as I go.  Maybe the Abilify will kinda level that out, without stopping the awesome progress I've made today.

So June is more than halfway over and, while no one has injured themselves (thank goodness), it's still been pretty busy.  We are fast approaching both pixie preschool graduation and pixie birthday party time.  She's having her party at one of those places that has giant inflatable bouncy things and slides.  Bonus that the adults can also go on them =D  Of course my pixie, being one of the cool kids, has deemed her theme "How to Train You Dragon", since she loved the movie.  Although, she does not want to help the dragons; she wants to become a viking and slay them.  That's how she rolls.

On top of all the pixie planning, I am off the lithium.  My tremors were definitely increasing, plus J noticed my left eyebrow kept twitching.  Also, I was experiencing, what I think were, mild hallucinations - visual, auditory and tactile.  Pdoc says last part wasn't possible, but they weren't there before the lithium increase.  I have a prescription for Abilify and I'm going to stay on the low dose of Ritalin.  I've been med free for about a week and mostly my symptoms are anger/frustration control and impulsivity issues.  I'm hoping the Abilify will help with that.

Writing has been slower than slow, but a few hundred words here and there is still progress.  I wish I could have some manic energy without any of the bad stuff so I could just accomplish the 7,000 task I wan to get done.

Do not read SPN spoilers when you have an entire freakin' summer to angst over them!

Also, what's with the Friday nights?  I may have to DVR it to watch Sunday  D:

So, last Friday I got a call from school that the pixie fell on the playground and her tooth went through her bottom lip.  Short story, we went to the ER, pixie got two stitches on the outside (none on the inside) and we took it easy Memorial Day weekend.  The doc took the stitches out yesterday and everything is looking good.

Now that both J and the pixie have been to the ER within a few weeks of each other, I think I'll avoid anything dangerous for awhile.

That was my excitement.  What's new with you guys?

xoxo
McKay

Pixie's pdoc says she fits the criterion for ADHD and wrote me a note to bring to today's meeting.  Between that and the information provided by myself and the special education teacher I have secured summer services for the pixie.  J says we deserve to go out and celebrate.  I say, "Show me the steak!"

It's warm and sunny. I heard the weekend will be gorgeous. Maybe I'll drag the family out to the beach at some point after slathering J in SPF 70 ;p The past two winters I've made trips down to Fort Lauderdale, FL, and it's been awesome. This year I was wondering if anyone would like to join me, make a group trip out of it. Would anyone be interested in maybe going? Also, J says he wants to send me on a trip to the UK as a birthday present (but I wouldn't necessarily be going in August). He wants me to look up pricing to get an idea of how much it will run, so he can work some extra overtime to pay for it. Any suggestions on a good time of year to visit? Met with the pediatric pdoc yesterday and he said based on the background I gave him, he definitely sees some OCD tendencies in the pixie. Today I will bring her in to meet with him so he can get a better idea of her problems. The special ed teacher that works with her explained that it will be hard to the the pixie summer services because her tests scores are high, but if the pdoc diagnoses her with ADHD or something else, we should be able to get them. My greatest concerns are that she won't be able to pay attention, or will become disruptive out of boredom. And even more than that, I want her to stop hurting herself when she's angry or frustrated. Also spoke to my pdoc yesterday and mentioned my concerns about Borderline Personality Disorder (BPD). She asked me what symptoms I thought I had and I showed her my checklist. Then she turns my chart around, points to the inside cover and explains that those were her impressions of me at my first visit. It said: bipolar II (which is the milder version - no full blown manic episodes), check into ADHD (which we did eventually and yes I have that), & strong BPD traits. She doesn't think it's a full blown case of BPD, but I have a lot of the symptoms. It doesn't respond well to meds, but therapy should work. When I talk to my therapist next week, and update him on my condition, I think it will help in where to focus my efforts to improve my negative behaviors. Also, I was finally able to articulate some of the problems I've been having with speech (can't remember simple words, using the wrong word). I explained I first noticed this on the Topamax, but it still seems to be a problem. Pdoc thinks it's either a bipolar symptom or a lithium side-effect. We're increasing the lithium, and if it gets better it's a bipolar thing, if it stays the same or worsens then the lithium is to blame. I've also been noticing more tremors lately. Yay meds D:
    Let's see, what else is going on:
  • and are trying to get me to write naughty things - lol
  • I've actually been working on my genderswap!Sam story
  • Planning a pixie b-day party - Theme: How to Train Your Dragon (she wants to be a viking!)
  • I'm actually being social this weekend :D

So Mom went home to California last Saturday and we made it about 32 hours until we got into trouble.  Apparently, since Mom was doing his chores for 3 months, J forgot how to wash the dishes and slipped with the big kitchen knife and cut his finger open.  From the bathroom I hear, "Help!  I need some help here!" and come out to find J holding his hand above his head, his finger wrapped in paper towels.  He didn't know how deep it was and was concerned about taking off the towels, so I called the ambulance (they're less than a mile from my house) and they came to take a look.  Luckily it wasn't too deep, but he still needed stitches.  J got to ride in to ambulance and the pixie and I followed behind in the car.

I've been taking good care of him, driving him back and forth to work, helping him in the shower (since he can't get the bandage wet), and making sure the pixie is gentle when she tackles him.  His stitches come out on Monday and he should be as good as new.

<lj-cut text="In other news">In other news, I have growing concerns about the anger and aggression I've been feeling lately.  I'm not happy with the way I feel.  There never seems to be much of a middle ground between the depression and mania.  Also, the are some symptoms that don't really fit with the bipolar.  For awhile now I've been thinking that there has to be something else going on, so I'm going to talk with the pdoc on Monday.  I know I shouldn't try to self-diagnose, but I feel compelled to research everything.  I'm leaning toward Borderline Personality Disorder.  That seems to fill in some of the gaps.  I guess I'll see what the pdoc says.

Also on Monday, I see the pediatric pdoc to give him info on the pixie and some of her behavioral problems.  On Tuesday she'll spend some time with the doc and then Wednesday I'll hopefully have enough info to give the school so they'll continue services throughout the summer (instead of making the pixie wait until the Fall).  And of course, to top things off, they'll only be half-day kindergarten in Sept. because of budget cuts.</lj-cut>

So, yeah, never a dull moment with <lj user="mckays_girl"> & Co.

Okay, so I'm going to try to update more often and not just fic.  I want to be better about sharing what's going on in my life.

<lj-cut text="May be triggery for those with mental health issues">In February, I really thought I was pulling out of the depression and was all set to enjoy spring.  Things didn't work out that way and I was dragged further down.  There were some very low points this winter.  It was one of my worst since college.  There were days that I wanted to die, wished that something bad would happen so I didn't have to deal with life anymore.  I was just so tired of expending all of my energy on day to day things that seemed so simple to everyone else.

I think part of the problem was that work got cut down to 2 days a week.  Now, I don't love my job by a long-shot, but it gave me a reason to get out of bed every morning.  At first, I was excited by the "vacation", being home 3 days a week sounded great in theory - I was going to write and exercise and get some projects done around the house - in theory.  It wasn't long before I was sleeping in, skipping showers, and generally feeling like there was no use for my existence.  It all sounds pretty over-dramatic looking back, and even at the time there was a small, rational corner of my brain reminding me to just hang on until spring.

Spring took a long time in coming.  The weather was terrible; we had more snow than usual.  My vacation with J even got rescheduled because our flight was canceled due to the snow.  Things seemed to drag on and I felt so helpless, so out of control.  I was overwhelmed by all the little details of my life and couldn't find joy in my usual hobbies.  The only thing that kept me going was that I felt like J and the pixie couldn't function without me, didn't know how to run the household.  It wasn't that I felt that they would miss me (even though the little rational corner tried to remind me).  I felt like a burden to J and like I did more harm than good for the pixie with all my mood swings.

I had to carefully word everything I told my doctors, because I knew where I would end up.  Hell, a couple of weeks in the hospital would have probably done me some good, but I know J needed me around.  I also avoided contact with all of my friends, trying not to burden anyone else with my problems.

I spent 4 month like that, feeling alone but unable to reach out.  I didn't know how else to handle it.  Honestly, I still don't know if the cycle will continue to repeat, but it's good to know that you guys will still be around when I manage to get my ass in gear and sign on.

Now I'm definitely in the upswing, probably slightly manic.  I'm writing, which makes me incredibly happy.  I just have to watch out for all the other fun signs that can ruin all my joy.  I'm still feeling lonely.  It bothers me that the only way I seem to connect to people is online, that I'm still so unsure of myself.  I'm still tired of dealing with the symptoms, of not fulfilling my potential, of not meeting my goals.  I know I'm too hard on myself, and I'm trying to figure out why.  That may be the real key to happiness as I learn to accept my faults and embrace my strengths.

So, that's what I been up to over the winter.  Comment?  Questions?  Vodka?
